    <h1>Reykjavik</h1>
    <p>Iceland is a land of breathtaking natural beauty and otherworldly landscapes, making it a must-visit destination for any adventurous traveler. From majestic waterfalls and geysers to volcanic landscapes and geothermal hot springs, Iceland offers a unique and diverse range of natural wonders. The country's vibrant culture and rich history, including its Norse mythology and folklore, add an extra layer of fascination to the experience. Whether it's the chance to witness the mesmerizing Northern Lights, explore ice caves, or soak in the soothing waters of the Blue Lagoon, Iceland promises an unforgettable and truly immersive travel experience that's unlike any other destination in the world.</p>

    <h2>Top Attractions</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <h3>Black Sand Beaches</h3>
            <img src="https://placehold.jp/400x150.png" alt="">
            <p>Iceland's black sand beaches are a stunning natural wonder, created by volcanic activity and the erosion of dark volcanic rocks. The contrast between the black sand and the surrounding landscape of rugged cliffs and crashing waves makes these beaches truly mesmerizing.</p>
            <a href="https://guidetoiceland.is/travel-iceland/drive/reynisfjara"a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Geysir Hot Springs</h3>
            <img src="https://placehold.jp/400x150.png" alt="">
            <p>Iceland is home to some of the most impressive geysers in the world, with the most famous one being Strokkur in the Haukadalur Valley. This powerful geyser erupts every 5-10 minutes, shooting boiling water up to 40 meters into the air, creating a spectacular display of nature's force.</p>
            <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/XKSzBZyPsYi82oPA6">
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Ice Caves</h3>
            <img src="https://placehold.jp/400x150.png" alt="">
            <p>Hiking inside Iceland's caves is a thrilling and otherworldly experience. As you venture deeper into the dark, mysterious chambers, you'll encounter stunning ice formations, unique geological features, and perhaps even glimpse the mesmerizing blue ice that makes these caves so famous.</p>
            <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/VnUgPYcZdaisfMMB8"a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Northern Lights</h3>
            <img src="https://placehold.jp/400x150.png" alt="">
            <p>One of the most enchanting natural phenomena in Iceland is the aurora borealis, also known as the Northern Lights. Visitors to Iceland have the opportunity to witness this mesmerizing display of colorful lights dancing across the night sky, creating a magical and unforgettable experience.</p>
            <a href="https://guidetoiceland.is/the-northern-lights/how-to-find-the-northern-lights-in-iceland"a>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Iceland Travel Tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Pack waterproof shoes</li>
        <li>You don't need to tip</li>
        <li>Most roads are one lane</li>
        <li>Don't get your hair wet in the Blue Lagoon</li>
        <li>Avoid taking a taxi from the airport</li>
        <li>Bring a rain jacket/umbrella</li>
    </ul>

